Team 2485 the W.A.R. Lords and Team 346 the RoboHawks are proud to present our second annual Summer CADathon collab, FISH FRENZY!! Participants will have this opportunity to practice their design and CAD skills with a new mock FRC game --anyone is welcome!

Kickoff will begin at NOON PST on July 20, 2024 and the CADathon will run until 11:59pm PST on August 10, 2024 (3 weeks)

Join our CADathon server to gain access to the game (on 7/20), collaborate with others, and get your questions answered!

CADathon Server link (again): Summer 2023 CADathon

Welcome to the 2024 summer CADathon: Fish Frenzy. This Google Drive folder has both the field CAD and Game Manual:

https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1C7KvdMad26XTSju2qNGy7GRzrY5LZNVP

If you have any questions, you can ask in the qna section of the discord server, where we will get back to you as soon as we have an answer. Additionally, we will release updated Game Manuals if any problems become apparent with the original. Submissions for robots will be though a google form, which will be released later, and are due on August 10th.

Hey all, we’re one week into the CADathon and going strong! If you haven’t already, we’d recommend moving away from the planning stage, and towards the modeling stage this week. The game manual can be found below, but we recommend that you join the discord server so that you can receive game manual updates, ask questions, and see what other participants are working on.

Version 1.3 of the game manual: 2024 FISHING FRENZY Game Manual v1_3- Google Docs.pdf - Google Drive

Discord Server link: Summer CADathon

Good luck to you all, and feel free to ask any questions, big or small (preferably through the server)!

4303 The Last Dance

4303 would like to share our robot here because we didn’t have time to make a tech binder. We won best mechanism for our end effector, which we are very excited about!

CAD

Members:
@Eliot @George_Tao @Jupiter @CyberClone @Curtis @bcon @Takanori

Full Robot3296×2547 2.17 MB

End effector

The end effector has a magazine-inspired design, allowing it to hold up to three pellets or two pellets and one coral. It’s powered by one Kraken X60 with a double sided belt. Its bent sheet metal frame allows it to be very light.

Full Robot (9)3296×2547 2.18 MB

Full Robot (8)3296×2547 2.27 MB

Intake

The intake is driven by one Kraken X60, with one super wide belt and one large roller. This provides us with a large acquisition area for pellets. The pivot is also driven by one Kraken X60.

Full Robot (3)3296×2547 1.81 MB

Arm

Our arm is powered by four Kraken X60s. Two for the first joint, one for the second, and one for the wrist. The joints are both controlled by custom gearboxes built into our drivebase. It can score pellets high and intake from the ramp loading station.

Full Robot (4)3296×2547 1.46 MB

Arm3296×2547 2.49 MB

Climb

The back stinger is powered by two Kraken X60s on a rack and pinion. We climb with the stinger and the intake working together.

Climber3296×2547 1.85 MB

Field3296×2547 2.05 MB

Drivebase

Our drivebase is controlled by four Z.4n custom swerve modules designed by @George_Tao.

Full Robot (6)3296×2547 3.49 MB
